Filtering steps
---

(1) array: (nlabel, ntheta, nlambda)
    - each (:,i,j) is convolution with one specific wavelet kernel (morletCoeff)
(2) reshape array: (nlabel, ntheta*nlambda)
(3) along axis=1, get array index with maximum magnitude
(4) get associated convolution coefficient (morletCoeff, magnitude, real, imag, phase), lambda and theta: (nlabel)
(5) choose "expected value" across wavelets (weighted average): (nlabel)
    - expectedTheta = sum(theta*morletCoefficient)_over(lambda,theta)/sum(morletCoefficient)_over(lambda,theta)
    - expectedLambda = sum(lambda*morletCoefficient)_over(lambda,theta)/sum(morletCoefficient)_over(lambda,theta)
